[{"location":"api/#API","page":"API","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"The one function you need to convert URNs to URLs in a markdown source:","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"rewrite","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#CiteDown.rewrite","page":"API","title":"CiteDown.rewrite","text":"Rewrite contents of file f with URNs replaced by URLs if they are configured for citable services in the file's YAML header.\n\nrewrite(f)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"A publicly exported function so that linkedMarkdownImage can work from a URN and a CiteDown.Settings instance.","category":"page"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"linkedMarkdownImage","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#CitableImage.linkedMarkdownImage","page":"API","title":"CitableImage.linkedMarkdownImage","text":"Compose markdown wrapping IIIF URL for image linked to an image citation tool installation.\n\nlinkedMarkdownImage(ict, img, service; ht, caption)\n\n\nArguments\n\nict URL of an instance of the CiteArchitecture ImageCitationTool.\nimg Cite2Urn for an image.\nservice IIIFService\nht Height of resulting image in pixels.\ncaption Caption to embed in resulting linked markdown string.\n\n\n\n\n\nCompose markdown wrapping IIIF URL for image linked to an image citation tool installation.\n\nlinkedMarkdownImage(img, cdsettings)\n\n\nArguments\n\nimg URN string\ncdsettings CiteDown.Settings\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#Internal-structures-and-functions","page":"API","title":"Internal structures and functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"CiteDown.Settings","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#CiteDown.Settings","page":"API","title":"CiteDown.Settings","text":"Settings for interpreting URNs in markdown.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"CiteDown.pageparts\nCiteDown.settings\nCiteDown.null_settings\nCiteDown.urlize","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#CiteDown.pageparts","page":"API","title":"CiteDown.pageparts","text":"Split markdown file into YAML header and markdown body. Returns a tuple of 2 strings.  If there is no YAML header,  the first string will be empty.\n\npageparts(f)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#CiteDown.settings","page":"API","title":"CiteDown.settings","text":"Create document settings object from a string source.\n\nsettings(src)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#CiteDown.null_settings","page":"API","title":"CiteDown.null_settings","text":"Initialize a Settings instance with empty values.\n\nnull_settings()\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"api/#CiteDown.urlize","page":"API","title":"CiteDown.urlize","text":"Convert URNs in markdown image references to URL values.\n\nurlize(md, cdsettings)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#CiteDown.jl","page":"Guide","title":"CiteDown.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#TL;DR","page":"Guide","title":"TL;DR","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"Write markdown text with links to citable content identified by URN; configure sources for retrieving citable content in a YAML header; resolve URN values to content referred to by URLs.","category":"page"},{"location":"#What-it-is","page":"Guide","title":"What it is","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"Markdown is a light-weight, practical format for expressing the structure of textual content.  Cite2Urns and CtsUrns are technology-independent formats for identifying scholarly resources.  The CiteDown.jl package lets you identify linked content in markdown documents with URNs.  You can separately configure sources for resolving the URNs and linking to or embedding content cited by URN in a new, resolved markdown document.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"In version 0.1.x, the CiteDown package supports the use of Cite2Urns to cite images.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Citation-of-images-in-markdown","page":"Guide","title":"Citation of images in markdown","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"URNs may be used in image references, to embed an image in the document, or in generic links.  ","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"Here's a markdown example of an image reference (image would be embedded on the page in markdown-aware applications):","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"The first page of the *Iliad*:  \n\n![illustration](urn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.2017a:VA012RN_0013)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"Here's a markdown example of a generic link (image would be treated as a hyperlink in markdown-aware applications):","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"[this page](urn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.2017a:VA012RN_0013)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"Image URNs may include extended citation to identify a region of interest on the image, as in this markdown example:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"A one-line summary of the first book appears in \n[this image](urn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.2017a:VA012RN_0013@0.1554,0.09733,0.3975,0.02652).  \n\nHere it is embedded in the current page:\n\n![detail](urn:cite2:hmt:vaimg.2017a:VA012RN_0013@0.1554,0.09733,0.3975,0.02652)","category":"page"},{"location":"#Configuring-a-YAML-header","page":"Guide","title":"Configuring a YAML header","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"Example:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"---\nict: \"http://www.homermultitext.org/ict2/?\"  \niiif:\n    service: \"http://www.homermultitext.org/iipsrv\"\n    path: \"/project/homer/pyramidal/deepzoom\"\nmaxheight: 500\n---","category":"page"},{"location":"#Generating-new-markdown-resolved-to-URL-values","page":"Guide","title":"Generating new markdown resolved to URL values","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"repository = pwd() |> dirname |> dirname","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"The rewrite function takes a file name, and composes a new markdown string.  Compare the source file with the rewritten version.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"Source:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"mdfile = joinpath(repository, \"test\", \"data\", \"img.md\")\nread(mdfile, String) |> print","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"Rewritten:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Guide","title":"Guide","text":"using CiteDown\nwithurls = rewrite(mdfile) \nprint(withurls)","category":"page"}]
